HEADWORD: Yataghan
<hw>Yat"a*ghan</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Turk.
<ets>y⟦amac⟧t⟦amac⟧gh⟦amac⟧n</ets>.]</ety> <def>A long knife, or short
saber, common among Mohammedan nations, usually having a double curve,
sometimes nearly straight.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>ataghan</asp>, <asp>attaghan</asp>.]</altsp>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
